result.execSummary:
The defendant Andy J. Roxbury was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Case called @ 1:32 p.m. Defendant Andy J. Roxbury in court.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant advised of right to counsel and expertise.  Voluntary waiver of counsel accepted by Court.  Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. Plea: Ct 3 - NC.  Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Cts 1 & 2 - DRI.  Statement by DE. Court orders: 2 days WCJ - 2 days CFTS - Time served sentence, Costs w/ 60 DTP or PP.  Appeal rights given.

10:24 am case called. Defendant Andy J. Roxbury in court.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Statement by ADA Anderson regarding potential resolution-requests time for defendant to obtain his license.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for April 1, 2016 at 01:30 pm.

No operation of any motor vehicles without a valid driver's license.    The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.

Case Called @ 1:37 PM: Defendant Andy J. Roxbury in court with attorney Ben Szilagyi, both appearing via video.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.    Per SPD:  Eligiblity will be determined by custody status.  ADA argues as to Signature Bond due to PO Hold.  SPD takes no position on bond.  The Court:  Orders $1000 Signature Bond w/conditions.  NGP received and entered.   STC Scheduled - NOH Given.  Court enters Riverside Ruling in favor of the State and probable cause finding as to each count alleged within the complaint.  Status conference scheduled for January 12, 2016 at 10:15 am.
